<HEAD>Teen Admits Killing Sex Attacker After 7 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-ager carried out a seven-year vendetta by
stabbing to death a man who sexually assaulted him and another boy
in 1982, police said.
   Joseph Wolske, 17, surrendered to police before dawn Sunday and
confessed to the 1988 slaying of 67-year-old Jay Petzold, who was
found dead in his Brooklyn apartment, police said. Wolske was
charged with murder.
   The Daily News quoted a police source it did not name as saying
Wolske arrived at Petzold's apartment, asking ``Remember me?''
   The teen-ager then forced his way inside, battered Petzold into
unconsciousness and stabbed him several times, the News said.
   In 1982, Petzold pleaded guilty to sodomizing 10-year-old Wolske
and an 11-year-old friend. The retired transit worker, who admitted
sexually abusing each boy several times in his apartment, was placed
on probation.
</TEXT>
