<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martha Reeves, who burned up the charts with her
recording of ``Heat Wave,'' thinks she's getting burned at the bank
by not getting royalties for the 1960s classic.
   The lead singer of Martha and the Vandellas sued Tuesday in Wayne
County Circuit Court Motown Records, its former owner Berry Gordy
Jr. and Jobete Music Co., asking for her share of royalties from the
