<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ivan F. Boesky, the one-time stock baron at the
center of Wall Street's fraud scandals, is pumping iron and growing
a beard at a California prison, a magazine says.
   Boesky also is tanned and jogs daily on the outdoor track at the
minimum-security federal prison camp in Lompoc, Calif., Manhattan
inc. reports in its July issue.
   The 52-year-old former stock speculator has served 15 months of a
three-year sentence for pleading guilty of conspiracy to lie to the
Securities and Exchange Commission over allegations of insider
trading. Boesky paid the SEC $100 million in alleged ill-gotten
profits and penalties in late 1986.
   The magazine quoted unidentified visitors to Boesky as saying he
has grown a full white beard and is ``impressively muscled.''
   ``Boesky works out every day at the outdoor weight area Lompoc
provides inmates, and he has built himself up substantially,'' the
magazine said.
