<SECOND>AM-Canada-Balloon Crash,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Baloon Plunges into Power Line Killing Pilot</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto CGY1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CALGARY, Alberta (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Residents of a quiet neighborhood watched
in horror Wednesday as a hot-air balloon in the shape of an ice
cream cone plunged into a high-voltage power wire and burned,
killing the pilot.
   Firemen extinguished the fire and police quickly cordoned off the
street. The name of the pilot, the balloon's only occupant, was
withheld until relatives could be notified.
   The balloon, fueled by propane burners, stood about three stories
high and was owned by Calgary Dairy Queen operators.
   The cause of the accident was under investigation, police said.
