<HEAD>London Shares Higher At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices moved higher Wednesday as the market
seemed unperturbed by the fall of the pound and a nationwide
transportation strike.
   Volume was low as today's national rail strike, combined with a
walkout by subway and bus drivers in London, left many brokerages
and institutions understaffed.
   Much of the trading volume was in the pharmaceutical and
electronics sectors, dealers said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 index was up 11.6 points,
