<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Heinz     06-21 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Heinz,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Heinz Reports Record Earnings, Sales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   H.J. Heinz Co. said Wednesday its
fourth-quarter earnings jumped 15.2 percent as its sales increased
11 percent.
   The food company reported earnings of $117.2 million, or 89 cents
per share, in the quarter ended May 3, compared with $101.6 million,
or 77 cents per share, for the same period a year earlier.
   Sales for the quarter jumped to $1.6 billion compared with $1.4
billion for the year-ago period, the company said.
   Improved volume in Italian baby food and Weight Watchers brand
food products, primarily in the United Kingdom, and higher prices
contributed to the sales increase, the company said.
   Net income for the full fiscal year increased 14 percent to $440
million, or $3.34 per share, compared with $386 million, or $2.91
per share, for fiscal 1988.
   Sales for the year totaled $5.8 billion, a 10.6 percent gain from
$5.2 billion recorded in 1988.
   Heinz said the sales increase was due to price increases,
significant volume gains, and acquisitions in the pet food area and
foreign markets.
</TEXT>
