<DOCNO> AP890621-0259 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-21-89 1642EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet2pm     06-21 0253</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0246</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was mixed today with some share
prices getting a boost from favorable indications about the Federal
Reserve's credit policy.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 3.79 to 2,476.67 by
2 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Losers held a slight lead over gainers in nationwide trading of
New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 621 up, 687 down and 569
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 112.77 million shares with two
hours left to go in the session.
   Analysts said a Fed report on economic conditions around the
country eased market concern that the central bank might need to
drive interest rates higher.
   The report, known as the ``beige book,'' indicated that growth is
slowing and inflationary pressures have eased in response to an
anti-inflation campaign waged by the Fed.
   Besides the economic concerns, many Wall Streeters lately have
speculated that stock prices might be due for a pause or pullback
after their strong advance since late last year.
   Among the blue chips, International Business Machines was up | to
110[, USX fell | to 36~ and General Motors was down \ to 40].
