<FIRST>r f AM-SmithKline-Beecham     06-21 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-SmithKline-Beecham,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>SmithKline Schedules Shareholders Meeting on Proposed Merger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shareholders of SmithKline Beckman Corp. will
meet July 26 to vote on a proposed merger already approved by
shareholders of its proposed merger partner, Britain's Beecham Group
PLC.
   SmithKline also announced Wednesday it has received permission
from the federal Securities and Exchange Commission to distribute
proxies on the question.
   Stockholders of Beecham, which produces health-care and
personal-care products, approved the merger Tuesday.
   Officials of the two companies agreed in April to combine into
the world's second-largest producer of prescription medicines and
over-the-counter remedies.
   If SmithKline shareholders approve, the merger is expected to
take place later this summer.
   The proposed merger of SmithKline and Beecham would be carried
out through an exchange of stock and a spinoff of several
non-pharmaceutical companies to create a new company, SmithKline
Beecham, with headquarters in London and offices in Philadelphia.
   Based on 1988 sales, the new company would have annual revenues
of about $6.7 billion.
</TEXT>
