<FILEID>AP-NR-06-21-89 2049EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-IntelsatChairman     06-21 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Intelsat Chairman,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Parapak Elected Intelsat Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Indonesian satellite executive Jonathan Parapak
was elected chairman Wednesday of the International
Telecommunications Satellite Organization.
   The Intelsat board of governors, meeting this week in Washington,
also named American executive Bruce L. Crockett as vice chairman.
   Each will hold one-year terms, ending in June 1990.
   Parapak has served as Intelsat vice chairman since June 1988. He
is the president of P.T. Indosat, the state-owned company for
international telecommunications in Indonesia. He also is the
governor for ASEAN Group I, representing the Intelsat signatories of
Indonesia and Singapore.
   Crockett is president of the world systems division of the
Communications Satellite Corp. (Comsat), a position he has held
since 1987. He oversees Comsat's participation in Intelsat and the
International Maritime Satellite Organization.
   Comsat is the U.S. signatory to Intelsat, which is a non-profit
cooperative of 117 member nations that owns and operates the global
communications satellite system used worldwide by countries for
their international and domestic communications.
   Intelsat is the major provider of transoceanic telephone and
television services.
</TEXT>
