<FIRST>r f AM-US-Agriculture     06-21 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US-Agriculture,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Career Employee Named To Head Foreign Agriculture Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A careeremployee, Rolland E. Anderson Jr., has
been named to head the U.S. Agriculture Department's Foreign
Agricultural Service.
   Anderson, a native of Iona, Minn., and an agricultural economics
graduate of South Dakota State University, has more than 25 years of
experience representing U.S. agricultural interests overseas,
Agriculture Secretary Clayton Yeutter said Wednesday.
   ``His distinguished service qualifies him uniquely to lead FAS
during this important period of negotiation for reform in world
agricultural trade,'' Yeutter said.
   Anderson, who goes by the nickname Bud, has had assignments as
agricultural attache at U.S. embassies in Britain, the Netherlands,
New Zealand and West Germany.
