<FIRST>r f BC-Pennwalt-Acquitaine     06-21 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Pennwalt-Acquitaine,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Aquitaine Extends Pennwalt Offer For Third Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Elf Aquitaine Inc., which has agreed to buy
Pennwalt Corp. for more than $1 billion, extended its offer of $132
per share for two weeks Wednesday.
   The extension was the third, with Aquitaine in each case saying
more time was needed to comply with the Federal Trade Commission's
request for information and documents about the deal.
   The French government-controlled oil and chemical company said in
a news release it expects to submit all the documents to the FTC by
next week.
   As of noontime Wednesday, Aquitaine had acquired at least 4.31
million shares of the U.S. chemical company. At the time the deal
was announced, Pennwalt had about 8 million common shares
outstanding.
   The deadline, which had been set for Friday, was extended to 5
p.m. July 7.
   Pennwalt agreed to the purchase March 20 to thwart a hostile
takeover attempt by Centaur Partners. Three days after the agreement
was announced, Centaur ended its $110-per-share offer for the
company.
   Pennwalt's stock closed up $1.37{ on the New York Stock Exchange
on Wednesday at $128.75. The extension was announced after the
market closed.
</TEXT>
